The global community today beams an unprecedented searchlight on biases women face in the cause of building the nation, as the world commemorates International Women’s Day (IWD) 2022. Nigeria, as a member of the global community, should show more than a passing interest in challenging those factors that impede the social, economic, cultural and political progress of women. Indeed, the country has not shown an admirable record in women’s affairs but the time is ripe to break the glass ceiling.  